			>
			<div></div><div></div><div>"What is an acceptable dps loss from dual wield and 2h fighting to use a 1h/shield set up?"<br><br>AGGRO:<br>The ability, like Knights, to use an endurance/mana fueled at-will ability to offset aggro loss.<br><br>Except that IMO Knights benefit in their raid roles by faster-refreshing and retargetable "snap aggro". AND Warriors must have the ability to obtain and hold aggro with all of their weapon configurations as a raid MT from the start to the end of fights.<br><br>The best solution IMO is either Warrior Shieldmate aggro weapons with higher than normal procratemods, a built-in Warrior ability that increases procrate when using a shield, etc.<br><br><u>No</u> loss in aggro that can not be completely compensated for by increased use of at-will aggro disciplines (not good for Knights IMO) OR no loss at all.<br><br>DPS:<br>No greater loss in <u>total class power</u> than Knights experiance. I worked long and hard to be the best Wariror I can. It is discouraging
beyond belief to equip a shield and watch your secondary role (as
little of a secondary role that is) (and your primary role) go down the
loo.<br><br>"I want to know in given situations, because different situations are different."<br>There to exist content where a group would look for a Warrior (or a Paladin, or an SK) in strong preferance to their competitors. For Warirors that content should be hard hitting mobs. It appears that Knights are already prefered in all other content.<br><br>In raids, less Simon Says/Musical Chairs content. I would prefer dungeon crawls with plenty of mobs for Knight plow tanks to handle, 6 adds that must be continually offtanked by knights and killed in turn. I just want to play a Wariror and FIGHT not read #%^&amp; emotes all night long or fight content like the Weaponry Trial ALL the time.<br><br>DPS<br>I KNOW how much DPS Paladins do vs. undead. My jaw has hit the floor when I've seen some max hits on a par or better than what the best nukers can manage. The thing is - I really am not jealous. BUT when the raid leader screems "UNLEASH HELL!" 30 second Fellstrike is beyond pathetic. A bone, there doesn't even have to be meat on it. Just a bone..... the smell of a bone, the rumor that bones exist - something!!!!<br><br>To me it all revolves around why a created a Wariror. OK, raid MTing was the big draw for me. But in groups I always used to seek out the hardest content. No more. SoE gutted my class. The shared my central defining ability, they designed content to favor Knights, they changed things so my central defining ability has no role in group content.<br><br>I group to get manditory raid flags for myself and others and to obtain salable loot and DoN crystals to gear up my 66 Paladin.<br><br>No hyperbole - if I wasn't a raid Warior I'd quit. And lemme tell ya, being a raid Wariror isn't anywhere near as rewarding as it was before the designers discovered Dance Dance Revolution and TankParity (and Knight Spellbook Superiority).<br></div><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>03-14-2006</span> <span class=time_text>04:19 PM</span>	
