<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=15392#M15392">4</a> of 830
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2389 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div><br><blockquote><hr>Abazzagaroth wrote:<br><div>Since the couple other long threads at the top of this forum have regressed to the point no one wants to actually &quot;discuss&quot; anything in lieu of insults, hyperbole, and gross generalizations, I thought I'd start a new thread.</div><div></div><div>-----------</div><div></div><div>A) TANKING</div><div></div><div><em>a) 1h/shield - Obviously a big issue with many warriors, so let's start here.</em></div><div><em></em></div><div><em>What are the perceived problems that have been raised?</em></div><div><em></em></div><div><em>1) Maintaining aggro</em></div><div><em>2) DPS loss</em></div><div><em>3) Loss in &quot;tanking&quot; advantage over knights who are using 1h/shield because points 1 and 2 make 1h/shield an unviable day to day solution</em></div><div><em></em></div><div><em>So my question here is, what do warriors envision a *feasible* solution is (use your opinion on what feasible means I guess, even though we all know there are knights and warriors that are completely ridiculous in their requests and expectations)?</em></div><div></div><div>To me a feasable solution is to create a modifier to a 1 handed weapon with a shield that in essence adds 2 things *only* when a shield is equipped in the offhand (it's clear that we can know when a shield is equipped in the offhand, as we get the little message that it's not if we try to bash without one).</div><div></div><div>It should add a certain percentage to the DMG of the weapon. I can't really say offhand what that percentage should be, that would actually require me to do some math, but I think that it would be quite fair to look at 2 handers as the standard by which similar 1 handers are compared when used with a shield.</div><div></div><div>Currently, the best 2 handers in the game are the Paladin and SK and Berserker epic 2.0's. Because those 2 handers exist, it's actually limited growth on warrior weaponry, as it would be patently unfair for warriors to be able to loot off of one mob a weapon which matched or exceeded the culmination of an epic quest. Warriors are just behind with either the Demiplane 2 hander, or the Vishimtar 2h Blunt.</div><div></div><div>All 2 handed weapons that warriors can wield at the very top, Paladins and SK's can also wield, meaning that only skillsets separate warriors from Knights, and only the 2.0's offer &quot;protected status&quot;, and this extends even into Demiplane.</div><div></div><div>I don't see an issue at all with saying that a warrior 1 handed epic 2.0 should also just as much outstat Knight accessible 2 handed weapons when linked with a shield. The current best weapons for Knights are either the Blade of Forgotten Faith/Morguecaller, or Eulogy. Taking Eulogy's ratio for now, at 85/35, a &quot;modified with shield 2.0&quot; should exceed that by a small margin. If you added 60% to the DMG of the weapon, it would be 74/29, which would exceed it by a small margin (0.391 for the epic 2, and 0.411 for the Eulogy). Looking at the ratios of other weapons if a 1.6x modifier were added, you'd have a sample:</div><div></div><div>Epic 1.5: 44/26</div><div>DoN Axe: 30+1/19</div><div>Despair: 38/21</div><div>Swiftcleave: 50/19</div><div>Dragonkiller: 54/21</div><div>Blade of Carnage: 24/20</div><div>Short Sword of the Ykesha: 13/24</div><div></div><div>Insofar as aggro loss is concerned, from procs... by removing the offhand weapon, we would lose roughly 33% of our proc based aggro, thus adding aproc mod of 1.25, we would experience a proc loss, but not a catastrophic one. </div><div></div><div>I think I could be happy with a 1.6x DMG mod and a 1.25x procrate mod when a shield is equipped.</div><div></div><div></div><div><em>What is an acceptable dps loss from dual wield and 2h fighting to use a 1h/shield set up?</em></div><div></div><div>Between 25 and 35%</div><div></div><div></div><div><em>What is needed in order to allow aggro to be maintained day to day in the 1h/shield set up? A feasibility caveat here would have to be something that didn't trivialize aggro in other set ups such that tank switching becomes super easy on raids, as apparently SoE finds a need to give warriors less than stellar aggro as some sort of raid strategy or some junk.</em></div><div></div><div>Tank switches are already trivial really, because of AE taunt.</div><div></div><div></div><div><em>What is an acceptable gap in tanking ability between warriors and knights? And don't through out some junk number, I want to know in given situations, because different situations are different.</em></div><div></div><div>This is a difficult question to answer, and it will require different solutions to the dilemma. I think that by fixing the shield block issue, you've gone a long way toward restoring the gap. The actual gap isn't too far off from the ideal when each class gets to use all weapon configurations, but the real issue comes with the messed up state that shield use for warriors is in, as it allows shields to be a &quot;gap closer&quot;.</div><div></div><div>The two areas of concern are &quot;upward scaling&quot; and &quot;downward scaling&quot;.</div><div></div><div>To prevent a massive advantage for warriors in single group content which we should not have, content should only very rarely favor disciplines such as defensive or evasive, and that content should not be a key to progression under any circumstance. In other words, the benefits of upward scaling mitigation advantage should really only be envisioned on raids and very rarely on single group content (there should be some, but not a lot).</div><div></div><div>With downward scaling on the other hand, warriors are in desperate need of something to compete with the power of stuns, Ward of Tunare, Tap AA's, self heals, and Decrepit Skin. We have two disciplines that should be retuned to provide this... Aura of Runes and Shocking Defense. Aura of Runes is almost identical to Decrepit Skin, only it's 1/4 the duration for many many many times the cost and has a super long refresh rate. The refresh should be lowered, the duration increased and the cost lowered. Shocking defense the same thing.</div><div></div><div>Insofar as gear is concerned, I'm of the belief that Sony needs to be consistent on gear. Either warriors should have a gear based advantage or we should not, and stick with it. The idea of switching every expansion between class specific and archetype specific gear sets really messes things up and causes a teeter totter effect, where in one expansion, such as DoD, Knights gained a TON on warriors because most of the gear fromDoD raid contentwas a lateral improvement for warriors and an upgrade for knights. When the corrective action is taken, possibly in PoRo, what happens is warriors take too large a leap forward.. if both start out at point A, and Knights go to Point B, and warriors go to Point C, that's not fair either.</div><div></div><div>If they want to say &quot;the gear should be the same and skills should reflect the difference&quot; then stick with it, and make the skills actually BE the difference. If they want to say &quot;Part of the warrior advantage is better gear&quot; then every single expansion we should be sporting better gear.</div><div></div><div>Warriors are not a generic melee class... we need warrior specific weaponry which reflects our role in EQ, not the role of everyone who can dual wield, or everyone who can wield a 2 hander. The prehistoric weapons that we're currently wielding is sheer insanity to me.</div><div></div><div></div><div><em>b) Endurance Regen</em></div><div><em></em></div><div><em>Not much to say about this, its insane they they haven't done anything about this, as there are a ton of things they could do to fix this &quot;problem&quot; in a matter of days, which begs the question of whether the devs simply do not want warriors to have good aggro control.</em></div><div></div><div><br>I cannot fathom why Endurance regen hasn't been added to the game. It really is a double penalty to have long reuse timers on our disciplines AND subject them to the terrible endurance regen.</div><div></div><div>A word about DPS... Vanquish REALLY doesn't bother me at all, as long as every mob or every 3rd mob isn't undead, because it turns from being a situational advantage to something that's basically most of the time, which then diminishes our position as &quot;the tank that does a ton of melee damage&quot;. I don't think I would like a version of Vanquish for some other mob type, that doesn't seem to fit within character for us, but I WOULD like a &quot;give it all you got&quot; massive single attack.</div><div></div><div>Now, here's the issue with that.</div><div></div><div>Harmtouch REALLY needs to be fixed in a big way. I do not want to, nor do I find it fair to even request to be able to do a large amount of damage via any means while SK's are still not the absolute kings of burst damage in tanking. They have a skill that can only be used once per hour or so that simply is way too weak in today's standards. A Paladin basically procs double of what harmtouch does every time he gets one of those nasty slays. I really don't like that at all. I don't feel comfortable asking for anything with a large hit, especially on an at will basis until SK's are actually causing measurable damage with their harmtouch. They should be head and shouders #1 among those who melee in what they can do in a single round if they so choose.</div><div></div><div>What I can do with some kind of cool at will burst damage thing should still be lower by a fairly dramatic margin from Harmtouch, but much higher than the max I can do now of about 4k IF I'm berserk AND under fellstrike and get lucky.</div><div></div></blockquote>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
