			>
			<div></div><br><blockquote><hr>Frodlin wrote:<br><div></div><br><blockquote><div></div><div><em>I think I could be happy with a 1.6x DMG mod and a 1.25x procrate mod when a shield is equipped.</em></div><div></div><div></div><div>only so long as the DMGbonus is only considered for aggro, and not actually damage output. Bash (which coincidently caps at higher skill than kick)is not too bad damage, its over 100, which isn't a bad thing.Anyway, the point of having a shield is improved toughness at the cost of dps, hence why a bash doesn't equal a double attacking secondary weapon+kick.</div><div></div><div><em>I cannot fathom why Endurance regen hasn't been added to the game. It really is a double penalty to have long reuse timers on our disciplines AND subject them to the terrible endurance regen.</em></div><div></div><div>Not really, our slow endurance regen has regenerated what we spent by the time our disc pop due to the long refresh time. I think they make it so that we cant spam defensive, dps, utility and aggro disc all the time, so we are either in tank mode or dps. However, I would like to say, it would be nice to have on the same timer as bellow/etc a DPS disc besides throw stone (either melee focus... or maybe life tap proc, cos this would aid our pitiful soloing slightly),adding such a disc would mean we could be in either dps mode or aggro mode, but never in both. This would better allow us to fulfill our secondary roll (dps) without exadurating our primary (keeping aggro/tanking).</div><div></div><div><em>but I WOULD like a &quot;give it all you got&quot; massive single attack.</em></div><div></div><div>but that would infringe on BS/frenzy of rogues/zerks</div><div></div><div></div></blockquote><br><hr></blockquote><p>to be honest, I am happy without a massive instant damage attack, 30 second burst dps is ok with me, but, as I said,it would be nice for our utility timer (the one with aggro on) to have dps alternatives for when we're not tanks, though I am not sure as how that could be implemented.</p><p></p><p>As a sidepoint, how come warrior shrouds get to have Snare/DoT/AC debuff, but we don't; is that to compensate for lack of procs? would be nice to get a AC debuff disc! and also while on the point of warrior shrouds, do the devs realise that bash is pointless without shield/slam (shrouds have neither)? if you shroud warrior/cleric you gotta illusion barb/ogre/troll just to be able to use bash! perhaps shrouds should come with a couple of weapon options 2fist on ele, sword+shield on humanoid/ 2hb+slam on bear? there is already variety on those shrouds, but would be nice for bash to actually be functional without use of illusion! ... sorry for that derail on shrouds... and yes i do know that the tank/healer shroud is pathetic after 50 or so (not decided exact level yet!).<br></p>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>If you're an idiot a horrible fate should await you. I don't want to play a game where every idiot can succeed and prosper. A game should reward people for being a good player, not for time investment alone. Progressive PvP Server Now Campaign. <br>(*copy into your sig to support*)<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
