		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I don't think it terribly appropriate to "debate" another Warrior's points of view on this thread - since it is in some ways a poll, so I'll resist the urge 8).<br><br>I do want to comment however how reasoned, fair, and in some ways conservative I find Frodlin's post. I differ really only in three respects:<br><br>1. I think classes that tank need to be able to "make-up" for aggro loss when using less than their optimum aggro setup - 2 of the 3 classes than tank can. I'm perfectly comfortable with it costing Warirors endurance, since it costs Knight's mana. However if we are going to pay for at need extra aggro, like Knights, it needs to be available when it's needed (at-will) like it is for Knights.<br><br>2. DPS is only part of total class power. I think loss of total class power needs to be looked at when deciding how much DPS a Warrior should do when using a shield. No hiding of still at 100% power spellbooks under the table.<br><br>3. SK Harmtouch needs to be addressed. However Paladins being at the top of quite a handful of raids in DPS is here today thanks to a powerful 5 minute long discipline (Fellstrike is 30 seconds). I don't think Warriors can fail to push for improvement despite SK's being badly off. I believe improvements in this area are urgently needed for <u>both</u> classes.<br><br>The problems presented by Knights having favorable ratio weapons, retaining almost all of their total class power, and getting a "gap closer" with shields doesn't effect only PoR hunting raid Warriors. Yes, it's probably as bad as it gets at level 70, but at level 66 my Paladin alt still falls down on his kness daily and thanks the Great Knight Intercessor at SoE.&nbsp; /hug Shield of Strife/Hopebringer and stunnable content.<br><div></div>	
		</td></tr>
