			<div></div><p>note this all comes down to NET desirability .</p><p>since sony has decided that all should be viable tanks , and have equal desirability as stated in reenvisionment .</p><ol><li>you cannot change warrior survivability or content such that knights cannot achieve the survivability.</li><li>the gross difference between warriorsurvivability +aggro must be similar to knightsurvivability +aggro</li><li>warrior other abilities MUST become as desirable as knight other abilities .</li></ol><p>since it says in all grouping situations and 2 person groups are as viable as 6 person groups you mustpresume that solo is also some form of grouping if you extrapolate the numbers . this means warriors should be allowed to solo at least as well as knightsALONG ALL LEVELS OF PROGRESSION, or at least acheive solo abilities as good as either knights ability to solo .</p><ul><li>since sony now has a position where survivability must be equal , then we can presume that warriors other role (dps) +aggro must become as desirable knight spellbook +aggro.</li><li>since spellbooks can achieve greater aggro more reliably than warrior taunt + melee + proc aggro then dps abilities of warrior must be great enough to by itself eclipse knight spellbook advantage .</li></ul><p>thats the need .</p><hr><p>this is the want :</p><p>since knights can achieve similar survivability in their most common configuration as warriors can in their most common configuration, knight spellbook advantage while tanking should be nullified and the dps advantage of warriors is made great enough to equal spellbook advantage when not tanking , OR warriors should getunique advantages that negate spellbook advantage ,OR warrior survivability should be great enough so that warrior canachieve survivabilityanywhere anyother class can achieve survivability .OR the dps advantage of warriors should be greater than the spellbook advantage enough that the aggro advantage of knights is nullified .</p><p>it all comes down to the most basic group which is currently 2 person , but can be extrapolated to soloing . if a knight can 2 person group content reliably then a warrior should be able to be substituted for the knight and have equal survivability and desirability .</p><p>thats equal desirability .</p>	
