			>
			<div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div>Shammo wrote:<br>"<span>As knights shouldn't be able to tank raid content as well as you
do, nor should you solo as well as them either. This is the trade off
and this is how it currently is, and I have yet to see anyone prove
otherwise."</span><br><br>The tradeoff was, as pointed out in the Warrior Class description, being the cornerstone of a good group with a consequence of greater group dependancy. Raiding didn't have anything to do with it.<br><br>The idea was that Warrior survivability gave Warriors sufficient of an edge&nbsp; that it was the basis for our attractiveness to groups. That Knight utility, etc. would naturally give them greater soloing capability than Warriors and allow them to shine in groups - but not for the same reason Warriors shine (better tanking).<br><br>There was supposed to be a tanking reason to prefer the Primary Tank to a tank in a group,&nbsp; just as there are utility reasons to prefer a part caster to a 100% tank.<br><br>Tank Parity (and Knight Spellbook Superiority) doesn't work for a variety of reasons - this is one. The "democratic" idea of using Warrior tanking as the only measuring stick for Warrior, Paladin, and SK's fails utterly beause Warrior group utility &lt; Knight utility and it's this utility you can see at work when the three classes solo and in all less than the very hardest group content.<br><br>That's why our DPS cannot take the same percentage hit as Knights when we switch to sword and board. Knights don't get tanking like a Warrior PLUS free group friendly utility. Tank Parity (and Knight Spellbook Superiority) can't work, it has never worked, and it will never work.<br><br>When discussing Warriors and Knights, put the 2 1/2 ton spellbooks on the scale.<br><div></div><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>03-15-2006</span> <span class=time_text>02:46 AM</span>	
