			<div></div><p>Because knight dps is supposed to be 80% of a warrior's dps. We are ALL balanced against each other in some ways or another.</p><p>The best 2h weapons you can get for a level 1 is 32/36 and are super rare (30/35 dn weapons are very common though if you spend a day or two in DN). The best knight 1h weapons for a level 1 are 19/25 and 28/30, both of which are super rare, and the former is massively expensive. I don't think scepter of destruction or BoC is a fair thing to expect level 1-40 characters to have either. I especially think balance is important at this level of the game, because there is very little that distinguishes tanks from each other prior to level 40 (gimpy heals that are superceded by potions, dps is all almost the same due to skill caps, hp almost the same, gear available almost completely the same, etc). It needs to be considered.</p><p>As to the issue of level 70 dps disparity, My *opinion* is that 20-25% dps advantage to warriors is appropriate, and more than that isn't. *shrug* You're free to have a different opinion, of course, but I feel all tank classes should be balanced against each other for the jobs we do, not for soloing, but what we do in 99% of 95% of individual's play time: grouping and raiding. After all, we are all giving our opinions on what is fair, we definitely aren't going to agree 100% on all points.</p><p>I can understand the reasoning for warriors wanting to be a true melee dps class, just like I can understand many rangers' desire to be a tank. I just don't agree with it.</p><p></p>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
