			>
			<div></div><p>Kahm,</p><p>Understand that the variance isn't with identical weaponry... rather is the range of increase. If I'm wielding a big ol 2h weapon, or dual wielding, I should be doing roughly 40% better damage than you if you're wiedling a 1h and shield. If I'm not, there's a fairly large problem. If you're wielding a big ol 2 hander and I've got 1h and shield I should STILL have a melee DPS advantage, but it should be fairly small.</p><p>The issue with epics is, epic weapons are supposed to be &quot;best of class&quot; through Depths at least. Knight epics absolutely have something to do with Warrior 2h weapons, whether they &quot;should&quot; or not, and a warrior 1 handed epic should in turn receive the same status as &quot;best of class&quot; in both dual wield mode (which it does) and in 1h/shield mode (which it does not, but that's due to the lack of implementation of mods yet).</p><p></p><p></p>
